result.execSummary:
All charges against Andrew Paul Terrell in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Andrew Paul Terrell is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 01:01 PM Defendant Andrew Paul Terrell in court with attorney Jens Hubert Loberg.  Kaley Walker appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 21CF44 and 22CF20 heard at this time. ADA Walker: amended information filed; guilty to amended charge in 21CF44 w/ court costs. Dismiss 22CF20. Victim's rights in compliance. Atty Loberg and Def agree.   Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant. Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to amened charge in 21CF44. Counsel stipulate to factual basis.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEFENDANT FREELY, VOLUNTARILY AND KNOWINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds Defendant guilty to amended charge in 21CF44. Dismisses 22CF20. ADA Walker and Atty Loberg addresss sentencing.  Court orders court costs ($443) and DNA sample w/in 30 days on amended charge in 21CF44. Defendant will pay today.   Appeal rights are given to the defendant. 1:15
